	<Title>
		Stress and headaches: Stop the cycle
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;Stress can make your head hurt, and a headache can really stress you out. Either way, you can rein in the pain. Consider these tips to keep stress under control, which can help prevent headaches: 1. Simplify your life. Ask yourself what really needs to be done and what can be dropped. 2. Get organized. Update your to-do list every day, both at work and at home. Delegate when you can. 3. Laugh. Humor is a great way to relieve stress. 4. Relax. When you feel your muscles begin to tense, breathe deeply. Focus on inhaling and exhaling deeply and slowly for at least 10 minutes.&lt;/p&gt;
